Colouration in ethanol: Chelicerae with irregular spots. Legs light yellow with black hairs and reddish-brown irregular markings. DS light yellow with irregular pattern consisting of dark spots and small patches of dark hairs, fovea and radial furrows distinctly marked. OS dorsally with yellowish- and reddish-brown patches, laterally spotted. OS ventrally lighter with reddish-brown marks arranged symmetrically (
Figs 15A–B
).

Colouration in ethanol: Generally as in male but DS reddish-yellow (
Figs 15C–D
).
